column5: Was wondering if anyone saw duo realis jerkbaits, luck e strike jerkbaits and lucky craft deep pointers at the show. I am looking for some. Thanks. Landry.
I think so...Not much of an answer I realize. I think Natural Sports and the next shop down had some or all of what your looking for.
I heard the duos r nice. I have had good success on the luck e strikes.
I haven't had a chance to try the Duo jerkbaits, but their topwater baits are killer!

I haven't seen the duo jerkbaits but hope to in the next week or so. I did read the rather lengthy review on them on Tackletour. They look really nice and I plan on adding some to my tackle box. I am a huge fan of Megabass 110's so I am hoping that the duo's are at least quality that won't cost me as much.
The luck e strike r a rip off of the 110's and they work great and r cheap.

The luck e strike r a rip off of the 110's and they work great and r cheap.  Just swap the hooks out and your good to go. Work better than my megabass. I loaded up on them last year when tackle warehouse had them for $4.99

ProJ has a wide variety of smallie jerkbaits at the show. Jackall, O.S.P,, Lucky Craft, Megabass, and Duo. Hard to find a better selection of brands and colours. They will be having a special deal today, go check them out.
I found the two duo colors I wanted and two luck e strike colors I needed to. It was a successful mission. Anyone ever fish the lucky craft pointer XD (extra deep)?
